        public ViewImageResponse renderImage(ViewImageRequest request)
        Description copied from interface: ImageRestService
        Will always attempt to render the image based on the request parameters. Does not perform the security checks, unlike ImageRestService.viewImage(ViewImageRequest).
        Specified by:

      • viewImage

        public ViewImageResponse viewImage(ViewImageRequest request)
        Description copied from interface: ImageRestService
        Returns the image matching the request parameters, only if the image passes the security checks. Either the resolution requested must match one of the registered resolutions for the context, or the security check callback returns true. The latter will only be used if the server is not operating in strict mode.
        Specified by:
        viewImage in interface ImageRestService
        Parameters:
        request - containing the parameters of the image
        Returns:
        response containing failure feedback or the resulting image
